---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy — oriz"
  description="What oriz collects, what it doesn't, and your rights."
  wordmarkSubtitle="legal"
>
  <header class="spine page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">oriz</a> / <a href="/legal/">legal</a> / privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="spine prose">
    <h2>Who runs this</h2>
    <p>
      oriz.in and every <code>*.oriz.in</code> subdomain are operated by Chirag Singhal, based in
      Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India. Contact:
      <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — aggregate page views and country. Cookieless.
        No personal identifiers.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Contact form</strong> — submissions go through Web3Forms which forwards them to my
        email. Web3Forms keeps copies; see their privacy policy.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Comments</strong> (where applicable) — handled by Giscus, which stores your comment
        in a public GitHub Discussion.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No accounts, no sign-in, no passwords — every site is fully public.</li>
      <li>No tracking across sessions for analytics (Cloudflare is anonymous).</li>
      <li>No selling of personal data to third parties.</li>
      <li>No newsletters unless you explicitly subscribe.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      We store no account data. To delete anything you submitted via the contact form or comments,
      email me.
    </p>
    <p>
      Under India's DPDP Act 2023, you have the right to access, correct, and delete your personal
      data. Contact the <a href="/legal/grievance/">grievance officer</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      oriz is not directed at children under 13. If you believe a child has provided data to us,
      contact the grievance officer for removal.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We will update this page when the practice changes, with the new date at the top. Material
      changes get a banner on the site.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
